\")\n\n# Now try ACTION7 to jump up\naction(['ACTION7'])\n\nseg = current_frame.segmentation\nnodes = seg['nodes']\n\nfor n in nodes:\n    if n['color'] == 'b':\n        rows = [r for r, c in n['boundary']]\n        cols = [c for r, c in n['boundary']]\n        print(f\"Char after ACTION7: rows {min(rows)}-{max(rows)}, cols {min(cols)}-{max(cols)}\")\n\npink_nodes = [n for n in nodes if n['color'] == 'P']\nfor p in pink_nodes:\n    rows = [r for r, c in p['boundary']]\n    cols = [c for r, c in p['boundary']]\n    print(f\"Pink: rows {min(rows)}-{max(rows)}, cols {min(cols)}-{max(cols)}\")\n\nprint(f\"Level completed: {last_action_result.get('level_completed')}\")\nprint(f\"Game over: {last_action_result.get('game_over')}\")\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "TOOL RESULT: python", "content": "Char: rows 37-40, cols 26-27\nChar after ACTION7: rows 37-40, cols 26-27\nPink: rows 19-21, cols 20-22\nLevel completed: False\nGame over: True", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}], "hasExactModelContext": false, "requestIndexWithinTurn": null, "messageCount": 0}, "context": {"sections": [{"label": "USER PROMPT", "content": "The code executed 1 action in the previous sequence.\nExecuted actions: MOUSE(row=20, col=21).\nYou are still on the same level.\nCurrent state: step 313, level 1.\nValid actions right now: LEFT, RIGHT, MOUSE, ACTION7.\nOnly tool: `python`. It receives `current_frame`, `previous_frame`, `history`, `transitions`, `last_transition`, `valid_actions`, `last_action_result`, and `action(actions)`. It also provides `last_animation` (per-action frames of your last `action(...)` call) and `frame_stats` (how much this game has animated so far) -- optional; use them only if you judge the intermediate motion informative rather than incidental.\nOnly letter-coded board views and lightweight metadata are exposed; raw numeric color IDs are not available.\nKeep tool output compact: use `current_frame.segmentation` as 